raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "xlwings" %}
{% set version = "0.27.15" %}
{% set sha256 = "9fcfbc00a2e0dcb4291c86e5816e31feefaff7e59a3c31f2c7bc73692b9469be" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 1
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv
  entry_points:
    - xlwings = xlwings.cli:main
  skip: true  # [py<35]

requirements:
  build:
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - pywin32  # [win]
    - psutil >=2.0  # [osx]
    - appscript >=1.0.1  # [osx]

test:
  commands:
    - xlwings -h
  imports:
    - xlwings
    - xlwings.conversion

about:
  home: https://www.xlwings.org/
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: Interact with Excel from Python and vice versa
  description: |
    xlwings is a BSD-licensed Python library that makes it easy to call Python from Excel and vice versa.
  doc_url: http://docs.xlwings.org/en/stable/index.html
  dev_url: https://github.com/xlwings/xlwings

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - fzumstein
